data.title: BCH spikes 16% to $545.20 on Fed rate cut, boosting risk-on mood in crypto markets. Derivatives activity rises. Potential breakout ahead.

data.title: Hill & Smith Inc. partners with Gregory Industries for integrated roadside safety solutions. Columbus, Ohio. Oct. 31, 2025.
data.description: Two prominent companies, Hill & Smith Inc., and Gregory, have joined forces to enhance roadside safety systems. The collaboration was disclosed in Columbus, Ohio, on October 31, 2025. Hill & Smith Inc. is renowned for producing advanced infrastructure and road safety products. This partnership signifies a mutual aim to provide a comprehensive and improved roadside safety solution.

data.title: Nasdaq leads charge; Dow Jones flat with Amazon and Apple rallying on strong earnings.
data.description: Today in the stock market, the Dow Jones index remained steady, showing no significant change. This was attributed to the strong performance of tech giants Amazon and Apple, which saw positive gains following robust earnings reports. Concurrently, the Nasdaq index led the charge, buoyed by Nvidia's CEO Jensen Huang highlighting the 'AI Virtuous Cycle.' This information was shared in a live coverage by Investor's Business Daily, highlighting the current dynamics within the market.

data.title: Vivakor sets new payment date for special dividend to Dec 31, 2025 due to government shutdown. Ex-dividend date was Sept 5, 2025.
data.description: In Dallas, TX, on October 31, 2025, Vivakor, Inc. (Nasdaq: VIVK), a company offering energy transportation, storage, reuse, and remediation services, has rescheduled the payment date for its special dividend to shareholders to December 31, 2025. The ex-dividend date was September 5, 2025. This change was made to allow for necessary communication and filings with the Securities and Exchange Commission, which cannot be completed during the current government shutdown. There is a possibility of further delays to the special dividend if the shutdown persists.

data.title: UNI OI drops 50% below moving averages. Uniswap at $5.71 with open interest down from $300M to $140M, reflecting cautious sentiment despite stable crypto market.
data.description: The trading price of Uniswap is currently at $5.71, which comes amidst a decrease in speculative trading. The open interest on the platform has also fallen significantly from $300 million to $140 million. This shift indicates a sense of caution in the market, despite the overall stability in the cryptocurrency sector.

data.title: Info-Tech Research Group provides blueprint for CJIS compliance amid struggling law enforcement agencies modernizing IT systems.
data.description: Numerous law enforcement and government organizations are facing challenges in meeting the continually changing CJIS security requirements as they upgrade their IT systems. A leading global research and advisory firm, Info-Tech Research Group, has unveiled a new blueprint called Build a CJIS Compliance Program. This blueprint aims to assist organizations in aligning with CJIS security mandates. It offers comprehensive guidance on establishing effective compliance measures.

data.title: Many workers won't receive raises in 2025; 25% promoted without pay increase; 50% companies anticipate layoffs in 2026.
data.description: A recent survey of 1,000 U.S. business leaders revealed that 25% of companies promoted employees without a salary increase. Additionally, nearly 50% of the surveyed leaders anticipate layoffs in 2026. These findings were reported by Resume.org, a prominent resume-building platform, in Kirkland, Wash., on October 31, 2025.

data.title: Dickinson College receives $20 million donation to establish "Jim Thorpe Center" addressing Native American boarding school history.
data.description: On October 31, 2025, in Carlisle, Pennsylvania, Dickinson College will establish the "Jim Thorpe Center for the Futures of Native Peoples" near the former site of the Carlisle Indian Industrial School (CIIS). CIIS, the first federally funded off-reservation boarding school in the United States, was created with the objective of forcibly assimilating Native American children and youth to "kill the Indian... save the man." The new center represents a powerful healing and corrective initiative.
